  "text": "The upstream connection pool overflow condition in Envoy v1.31.2 is defined and handled across several key C++ source files:\n\n**Overflow State Definition:**\nThe overflow state is defined in `envoy/common/conn_pool.h` (lines 96-105) with the `PoolFailureReason` enum which includes an `Overflow` value. This enum signals that a resource (connections or requests) has overflowed and policy prevented a new connection from being created.\n\n**Core Overflow Handling:**\nThe main logic for detecting and handling connection pool overflow resides in `source/common/conn_pool/conn_pool_base.cc`:\n\n1. **Connection Overflow Detection** (line 138 in `tryCreateNewConnection`):\n   - When `host_->canCreateConnection(priority_)` returns false, the code increments `host_->cluster().trafficStats()->upstream_cx_overflow_.inc()` to count connection pool overflow events.\n\n2. **Max Streams Overflow** (lines 175-180 in `attachStreamToClient`):\n   - When enforcing max requests and `host_->cluster().resourceManager(priority_).requests().canCreate()` returns false, the code calls `onPoolFailure()` with `ConnectionPool::PoolFailureReason::Overflow` and increments `upstream_rq_pending_overflow_` counter.\n\n3. **Max Pending Requests Overflow** (lines 282-287 in `newStreamImpl`):\n   - When `host_->cluster().resourceManager(priority_).pendingRequests().canCreate()` returns false, the code calls `onPoolFailure()` with `ConnectionPool::PoolFailureReason::Overflow` and increments the `upstream_rq_pending_overflow_` counter.\n\n**Resource Management:**\nThe resource limits are enforced by `source/common/upstream/resource_manager_impl.h` which implements `ResourceManagerImpl`. This class manages:\n- `connections_`: Maximum connections limit\n- `pending_requests_`: Maximum pending requests limit\n- `requests_`: Maximum active requests limit\n\n**Protocol-Specific Implementations:**\nDifferent protocol-specific connection pools inherit from the base `ConnPoolImplBase`:\n- HTTP/1: `source/common/http/http1/conn_pool.h`\n- HTTP/2: `source/common/http/http2/conn_pool.h`\n- HTTP/3: `source/common/http/http3/conn_pool.h`\n- TCP: `source/common/tcp/conn_pool.h`\nAll use the shared overflow detection mechanism in the base class.\n\n**Response Flag Handling:**\nThe response flag `UpstreamOverflow` is defined in `source/common/stream_info/utility.h` and is set when overflow conditions occur, allowing operators to identify overflow-related request failures in access logs and metrics."
